name: Louvre Museum
description: A famous museum located in Paris, France, home to the Mona Lisa.

name: British Museum
description: A museum in London dedicated to human history, art, and culture.

name: Metropolitan Museum of Art
description: One of the largest and finest art museums in the world.

name: Vatican Museums
description: The Vatican Museums display works from the immense collection amassed by the Roman Catholic Church.

name: Van Gogh Museum
description: A museum in Amsterdam dedicated to the works of Vincent van Gogh.

name: Uffizi Gallery
description: The Uffizi Gallery is a prominent art museum located adjacent to Piazza della Signoria in the Historic Centre of Florence in the region of Tuscany, Italy.

name: Hermitage Museum
description: A museum of art and culture in Saint Petersburg, Russia.

name: National Gallery
description: An art museum in Trafalgar Square in the City of Westminster, in Central London.

name: Museo del Prado
description: The main Spanish national art museum, located in central Madrid.

name: Rijksmuseum
description: A Dutch national museum dedicated to arts and history in Amsterdam.

name: Museo Nacional de Antropología
description: A national museum of anthropology in Mexico City.

name: Museum of Modern Art (MoMA)
description: An art museum in Midtown Manhattan, New York City.

name: State Tretyakov Gallery
description: An art gallery in Moscow, Russia, the foremost depository of Russian fine art.

name: National Museum of China
description: A museum of Chinese history and art, located in Beijing, China.

name: Musee d'Orsay
description: A museum in Paris, France, on the left bank of the Seine. It is housed in the former Gare d'Orsay.

name: Art Institute of Chicago
description: An art museum in Chicago, one of the oldest and largest art museums in the United States.

name: Guggenheim Museum
description: A museum of modern and contemporary art in New York City.

name: Tokyo National Museum
description: The oldest Japanese national museum, with a focus on traditional Japanese art.

name: Pergamon Museum
description: A museum in Berlin, famous for its monumental reconstruction of ancient buildings.

name: Israel Museum
description: The largest cultural institution in the State of Israel and one of the leading encyclopedic museums in the world.

name: Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History
description: A natural history museum located in Washington, D.C.

name: Museo Reina Sofia
description: A museum in Madrid, primarily dedicated to Spanish art.

name: Acropolis Museum
description: An archaeological museum focused on the findings of the Acropolis of Athens.

name: Museum of Fine Arts, Boston
description: One of the most comprehensive art museums in the world.

name: National Palace Museum
description: A vast collection of Chinese art and artifacts, in Taipei, Taiwan.

name: Shanghai Museum
description: A museum of ancient Chinese art, situated in the People's Square in Shanghai.

name: National Museum of Korea
description: The flagship museum of Korean history and art in Seoul, South Korea.

name: Museo Soumaya
description: A private museum in Mexico City and one of the largest collections of art in Latin America.

name: Musée du Louvre Lens
description: A branch of the Louvre located in Lens, France.

name: Museum of Egyptian Antiquities
description: Home to an extensive collection of ancient Egyptian antiquities.

name: Victoria and Albert Museum
description: The world's largest museum of applied and decorative arts and design, as well as sculpture.

name: Galleria Borghese
description: An art gallery in Rome, Italy, housing a substantial part of the Borghese collection of paintings, sculpture and antiquities.

name: The State Russian Museum
description: A museum in Saint Petersburg, Russia, dedicated to Russian fine art.
